annotation.TEXT: Yep, I've hitted the yelloh switch, so this levl will be easier!
Oh, yeah! I just realized something! It's possible to reach these inner two ? blocks now!
I'm just going to ignore any mushrooms that appear, since I already have two capes.
Alright, now let's head to the level on the right.
Finished! start is now 100% complete! On top of that, Yoshi's stomach should be full now (at least until I enter the next level)!
Watch out for the Chuck, although it was nice of him to open up a path to the P-switch in case you didn't want to bother hitting the turn blocks yourself!

Alright, so we have a tie between G and H. Hmm... I think I'll go for G (I want to see the half-switch get hit, too). Now, I'm going to injure myself on purpose so that my fireballs don't interfere...
Whoops! I already read that. Okay, we're almost done here...
There's orange soda down below, but it's completely inaccessable. Oh, well.

Just take the P-switch from the end of the level, and stomp it here. Then, use a kooper shell or cape spins to hit the inner two ? blocks! (Just be careful if you try cape spinning them, or the game might think you've gotten crushed and kill you.)
Hey, let's see how many glitched fish I can get on the screen at once here!
"field of koopas2"? That's gotta be a typo. I'm sure it meant "koopers" and not "koopas", so I'm still going to call them "koopers".
Instead, I'm going to raid all of these blocks with funny powerups. (Actually, they're just mushrooms.)
Okay, now there's a kooper. Don't kill him immediately, or it'll complicate things.
Oops... Well, I can always produce more.
Also, grab the remaining two Yoshi coins while you're here (yes, there are six in this level too).

Okay, now those ? blocks under the pipes there are not simple to hit. I'll get back to them in a moment. Also, you can pick up two more 1-ups here (or one 1-up and a Yoshi if you somehow lost your previous Yoshi).
In the meantime, let's stock up on feathers and 1-ups from these ? blocks! Yeah, unlike the original SMW, you can get feathers in world 1, which is really nice!
There's some more typos. I think they should be called "koopers". Well, let's explore the rest of this field field...
D'oh. A fireball managed to interfere anyway, but as long as I don't collect the resulting coin, I can get the kooper to respawn.
Also, don't worry. This house is magical. No matter how much I eat, it'll always be full of berries again after I leave and come back!
I think the midway gate was supposed to go here, but something glitched up with it, so this level effectively has no midpoint. Just be aware of that.
Demo count: 3
I still managed to get 40 stars, though, which means I just need 30 more for a bonus game!
Nope. Okay, let's go Yoshi, and collect some more coins that are conveniently placed in nice and neat rectangular holes in the land!
That opens the third level, but I'm not gonna go there today. I will, however, go back to start with Yoshi right now.
D'oh! Well, that didn't go as planned...
Now, let's chow down!

And there we go! Switch G is hit! But, truth be told, I didn't nail that on my first attempt. I first tried and failed about 20 times with the fire flower. Then I tried it small and got it on my second try. (Then, I tried about a dozen more times until I managed to jump off the switch after stomping it!)
Otherwise, certain people's OCDs may end up being bothered!
Now, just like in the original SMW, you can kick a shell from here and follow it to get some extra lives.
OM NOM NOM NOM NOM NOM NOM NOM NOM NOM NOM NOM NOM NOM NOM NOM NOM NOM NOM NOM NOM NOM NOM NOM NOM NOM NOM NOM NOM NOM NOM NOM NOM NOM NOM NOM NOM NOM NOM NOM NOM NOM NOM NOM NOM!!!
I'll be picking up this 1-up once again. Also, those should be your third and fourth Yoshi coins, if you've been collecting them all.
Also, you can stock up on more mushrooms here if you need them. Also, the yellow blocks will keep you from falling in this hole, which is nice!
Of course, it would help if I could hit the darned blocks!
And that's all the reachable stuff in here that I'm aware of, but if anyone knows how to get to the orange soda below, let me know!
Hi, Yoshi!
There we go! I knew you could do it, Mario!
Also, you can enter any of the first three pipes here, and they'll all take you to the same bonus room.
Oh, also, make sure you save a kooper shell so you can hit this one ? block.
I'll have to come back to this level later, when I'm capable of reaching them.
Maybe I shouldn't be recklessly kicking kooper shells...
I don't think any of these pipes can be entered, but I'll just double-check anyway.

In addition, I got 2 votes for 3-1, 1 vote for me to use savestates to press each switch and show off the rest of the game with each switch pressed (honestly, they all would have the same result), 1 vote for all of them at once, and 1 vote for switch I (under switch B).
Gee, I hope that shrinking myself in the switch level doesn't come back to bite me...
Huh, apparently there's a tiny ledge offscreen up there. Don't know what its purpose is, though.
There go all the blocks with funny powerups.
Hello, and welcome back to Chaos CompleXX! Here are the voting results for which switch I should press:
There's more coins under the land here that can't be reached... yet.
Well, that bites... Still, I got a 2-life combo! (3 if you count that 1-up mushroom!)
Okay, now using this kooper's shell, you can hit the leftmost and rightmost ? blocks that are under these pipes. However, the middle two cannot be hit right now.
Yes, we shoud go but really kill bowser now!
Hi! This message is different when you're riding Yoshi.
So, next time, I'll go "in the air of koopa" (that should be "kooper", but I'll let it slide this time since there's not enough room to spell out "kooper" there)! To be continued...
And, just like in the original SMW, you can use this P-switch to make a bridge which will let you reach the upper part of the goal more easily.
